# ğŸ“˜ API Documentation

---

# ğŸ”‘ AUTH APIs

---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ Register User
POST /api/auth/register


**Request Body**

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456",
  "role": "admin"
}


Success Response

{
  "error": false,
  "statusCode": 200,
  "data": {
    "_id": "65f2a1b3c9e4a6d123456789",
    "name": "Admin User",
    "email": "admin@gmail.com",
    "role": "admin"
  },
  "message": "Success"
}


## 2ï¸âƒ£ Login
POST /api/auth/login

**Request Body**

{
  "email": "admin@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456"
}


Response

{
  "error": false,
  "statusCode": 200,
  "data": {
    "token": "JWT_TOKEN"
  },
  "message": "Success"
}


ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ« ADMIN APIs

âš  Requires Admin JWT Token

Header:

Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>


## 3ï¸âƒ£ Add Student
POST /api/admin/students

**Request Body**

{
  "name": "John",
  "email": "john@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456",
  "department": "Computer Science"
}


## 4ï¸âƒ£ Assign Task
POST /api/admin/tasks

**Request Body**

{
  "studentId": "65f2a1b3c9e4a6d123456789",
  "title": "Build API",
  "description": "Implement CRUD using Node.js",
  "dueTime": "2026-02-20T23:59:59.000Z"
}

Response

{
  "error": false,
  "statusCode": 200,
  "data": {
    "_id": "65f3d21ac9e4a6d123456999",
    "title": "Build API",
    "description": "Implement CRUD using Node.js",
    "dueTime": "2026-02-20T23:59:59.000Z",
    "student": "65f2a1b3c9e4a6d123456789",
    "status": "pending"
  },
  "message": "Success"
}


ğŸ“ STUDENT APIs

âš  Requires Student JWT Token

Header:

Authorization: Bearer <STUDENT_TOKEN>


## 5ï¸âƒ£ Get My Tasks
GET /api/student/tasks

Response

{
  "error": false,
  "statusCode": 200,
  "data": [
    {
      "_id": "65f3d21ac9e4a6d123456999",
      "title": "Build API",
      "dueTime": "2026-02-20T23:59:59.000Z",
      "status": "pending"
    }
  ],
  "message": "Success"
}


## 6ï¸âƒ£ Mark Task Completed
PUT /api/student/tasks/:id


